The PR is based primarily off [this comment](https://github.com/yargs/yargs/issues/287#issuecomment-314463783) `console.log` calls as I could not find the relevant documentation. The following inspect code was used:

```typescript
const util = require('util');
function inspect(val: any): void {
  console.log(util.inspect(val, {colors: true, depth: 5}));
  process.exit(0);
}
```

As I could not find the documentation for a lot of these methods, I simply used generic any-based types to avoid incorrect definitions.

## getCommandInstance()

```
{ addHandler: [Function: addHandler],
  addDirectory: [Function: addDirectory],
  parseCommand: [Function: parseCommand],
  getCommands: [Function],
  getCommandHandlers: [Function],
  hasDefaultCommand: [Function],
  runCommand: [Function: runCommand],
  runDefaultBuilderOn: [Function],
  cmdToParseOptions: [Function],
  reset: [Function],
  freeze: [Function],
  unfreeze: [Function] }
```

### getCommands()

```typescript
[ 'format', 'test' ]
```

### getCommandHandlers()

```
{ format:
   { original: 'format',
     description: 'Format the given glob',
     handler: [Function: handler],
     builder: {},
     middlewares: [],
     demanded: [],
     optional: [] },
  test:
   { original: 'test',
     description: 'Exit with non-zero if any of the files are not formatted.',
     handler: [Function: handler],
     builder: {},
     middlewares: [],
     demanded: [],
     optional: [] } }
```

### hasDefaultCommand()

```typescript
false
```
